You have copied _all_ files from the SKIDROW folder to the installation folder? Try and run both the Launcher.exe and CoJ_TheCartel.exe as administrator. Remember also to block the game in the firewall so that it can't connect to the internet. When the procedure is done correctly, one should not need steam at all.

if the game won't autosave:

To be able to play the game again where you left off, you have to finish the chapter, you can not exit the game in the middle of the chapter because you will have to start that chapter again. The good thing is that chapters are not very long, 10 to 20 minutes (so far). Even every Level you gain when collecting money or secret agendas will be saved so don't worry
when you exit the game, the continue button is gone but it's OK, just choose Campaign, choose your character and the chapter (eg: Chapter 3, means you finished chapter 2 and ready to start chapter 3, when you collect Secret agendas in that chapter you will notice that the level you reached in chapter 2 will continue and not reset)
